110int ASN1_get_object(const unsigned char **pp, long *plength, int *ptag,
111 int *pclass, long omax)
112{
113 int i, ret;
114 long l;
115 const unsigned char *p = *pp;
116 int tag, xclass, inf;
117 long max = omax;
118
119 if (!max)
120 goto err;
121 ret = (*p & V_ASN1_CONSTRUCTED);
122 xclass = (*p & V_ASN1_PRIVATE);
123 i = *p & V_ASN1_PRIMITIVE_TAG;
124 if (i == V_ASN1_PRIMITIVE_TAG) { /* high-tag */
125 p++;
126 if (--max == 0)
127 goto err;
128 l = 0;
129 while (*p & 0x80) {
130 l <<= 7L;
131 l |= *(p++) & 0x7f;
132 if (--max == 0)
133 goto err;
134 if (l > (INT_MAX >> 7L))
135 goto err;
136 }
137 l <<= 7L;
138 l |= *(p++) & 0x7f;
139 tag = (int)l;
140 if (--max == 0)
141 goto err;
142 } else {
143 tag = i;
144 p++;
145 if (--max == 0)
146 goto err;
147 }
148
149 /* To avoid ambiguity with V_ASN1_NEG, impose a limit on universal tags. */
150 if (xclass == V_ASN1_UNIVERSAL && tag > V_ASN1_MAX_UNIVERSAL)
151 goto err;
152
153 *ptag = tag;
154 *pclass = xclass;
155 if (!asn1_get_length(&p, &inf, plength, max))
156 goto err;
157
158 if (inf && !(ret & V_ASN1_CONSTRUCTED))
159 goto err;
160
161#if 0
162 fprintf(stderr, "p=%d + *plength=%ld > omax=%ld + *pp=%d (%d > %d)\n",
163 (int)p, *plength, omax, (int)*pp, (int)(p + *plength),
164 (int)(omax + *pp));
165
166#endif
167 if (*plength > (omax - (p - *pp))) {
168 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(ASN1, ASN1_R_TOO_LONG);
169 /*
170 * Set this so that even if things are not long enough the values are
171 * set correctly
172 */
173 ret |= 0x80;
174 }
175 *pp = p;
176 return (ret | inf);
177 err:
178 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(ASN1, ASN1_R_HEADER_TOO_LONG);
179 return (0x80);
180}
181
182static int asn1_get_length(const unsigned char **pp, int *inf, long *rl,
183 long max)
184{
185 const unsigned char *p = *pp;
186 unsigned long ret = 0;
187 unsigned long i;
188
189 if (max-- < 1)
190 return 0;
191 if (*p == 0x80) {
192 *inf = 1;
193 ret = 0;
194 p++;
195 } else {
196 *inf = 0;
197 i = *p & 0x7f;
198 if (*(p++) & 0x80) {
199 if (i > sizeof(ret) || max < (long)i)
200 return 0;
201 while (i-- > 0) {
202 ret <<= 8L;
203 ret |= *(p++);
204 }
205 } else
206 ret = i;
207 }
208 /*
209 * Bound the length to comfortably fit in an int. Lengths in this module
210 * often switch between int and long without overflow checks.
211 */
212 if (ret > INT_MAX / 2)
213 return 0;
214 *pp = p;
215 *rl = (long)ret;
216 return 1;
217}
218
219/*
220 * class 0 is constructed constructed == 2 for indefinite length constructed
221 */
222void ASN1_put_object(unsigned char **pp, int constructed, int length, int tag,
223 int xclass)
224{
225 unsigned char *p = *pp;
226 int i, ttag;
227
228 i = (constructed) ? V_ASN1_CONSTRUCTED : 0;
229 i |= (xclass & V_ASN1_PRIVATE);
230 if (tag < 31)
231 *(p++) = i | (tag & V_ASN1_PRIMITIVE_TAG);
232 else {
233 *(p++) = i | V_ASN1_PRIMITIVE_TAG;
234 for (i = 0, ttag = tag; ttag > 0; i++)
235 ttag >>= 7;
236 ttag = i;
237 while (i-- > 0) {
238 p[i] = tag & 0x7f;
239 if (i != (ttag - 1))
240 p[i] |= 0x80;
241 tag >>= 7;
242 }
243 p += ttag;
244 }
245 if (constructed == 2)
246 *(p++) = 0x80;
247 else
248 asn1_put_length(&p, length);
249 *pp = p;
250}
251
252int ASN1_put_eoc(unsigned char **pp)
253{
254 /* This function is no longer used in the library, but some external code
255 * uses it. */
256 unsigned char *p = *pp;
257 *p++ = 0;
258 *p++ = 0;
259 *pp = p;
260 return 2;
261}
262
263static void asn1_put_length(unsigned char **pp, int length)
264{
265 unsigned char *p = *pp;
266 int i, l;
267 if (length <= 127)
268 *(p++) = (unsigned char)length;
269 else {
270 l = length;
271 for (i = 0; l > 0; i++)
272 l >>= 8;
273 *(p++) = i | 0x80;
274 l = i;
275 while (i-- > 0) {
276 p[i] = length & 0xff;
277 length >>= 8;
278 }
279 p += l;
280 }
281 *pp = p;
282}
283
284int ASN1_object_size(int constructed, int length, int tag)
285{
286 int ret = 1;
287 if (length < 0)
288 return -1;
289 if (tag >= 31) {
290 while (tag > 0) {
291 tag >>= 7;
292 ret++;
293 }
294 }
295 if (constructed == 2) {
296 ret += 3;
297 } else {
298 ret++;
299 if (length > 127) {
300 int tmplen = length;
301 while (tmplen > 0) {
302 tmplen >>= 8;
303 ret++;
304 }
305 }
306 }
307 if (ret >= INT_MAX - length)
308 return -1;
309 return ret + length;
310}
311
312int ASN1_STRING_copy(ASN1_STRING *dst, const ASN1_STRING *str)
313{
314 if (str == NULL)
315 return 0;
316 if (!ASN1_STRING_set(dst, str->data, str->length))
317 return 0;
318 dst->type = str->type;
319 dst->flags = str->flags;
320 return 1;
321}
322
323ASN1_STRING *ASN1_STRING_dup(const ASN1_STRING *str)
324{
325 ASN1_STRING *ret;
326 if (!str)
327 return NULL;
328 ret = ASN1_STRING_new();
329 if (!ret)
330 return NULL;
331 if (!ASN1_STRING_copy(ret, str)) {
332 ASN1_STRING_free(ret);
333 return NULL;
334 }
335 return ret;
336}
337
338int ASN1_STRING_set(ASN1_STRING *str, const void *_data, int len)
339{
340 unsigned char *c;
341 const char *data = _data;
342
343 if (len < 0) {
344 if (data == NULL)
345 return (0);
346 else
347 len = strlen(data);
348 }
349 if ((str->length <= len) || (str->data == NULL)) {
350 c = str->data;
351 if (c == NULL)
352 str->data = OPENSSL_malloc(len + 1);
353 else
354 str->data = OPENSSL_realloc(c, len + 1);
355
356 if (str->data == NULL) {
357 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(ASN1, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
358 str->data = c;
359 return (0);
360 }
361 }
362 str->length = len;
363 if (data != NULL) {
364 OPENSSL_memcpy(str->data, data, len);
365 /* an allowance for strings :-) */
366 str->data[len] = '\0';
367 }
368 return (1);
369}
370
371void ASN1_STRING_set0(ASN1_STRING *str, void *data, int len)
372{
373 OPENSSL_free(str->data);
374 str->data = data;
375 str->length = len;
376}
377
378ASN1_STRING *ASN1_STRING_new(void)
379{
380 return (ASN1_STRING_type_new(V_ASN1_OCTET_STRING));
381}
382
383ASN1_STRING *ASN1_STRING_type_new(int type)
384{
385 ASN1_STRING *ret;
386
387 ret = (ASN1_STRING *)OPENSSL_malloc(sizeof(ASN1_STRING));
388 if (ret == NULL) {
389 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(ASN1, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
390 return (NULL);
391 }
392 ret->length = 0;
393 ret->type = type;
394 ret->data = NULL;
395 ret->flags = 0;
396 return (ret);
397}
398
399void ASN1_STRING_free(ASN1_STRING *str)
400{
401 if (str == NULL)
402 return;
403 OPENSSL_free(str->data);
404 OPENSSL_free(str);
405}
406
407int ASN1_STRING_cmp(const ASN1_STRING *a, const ASN1_STRING *b)
408{
409 int i;
410
411 i = (a->length - b->length);
412 if (i == 0) {
413 i = OPENSSL_memcmp(a->data, b->data, a->length);
414 if (i == 0)
415 return (a->type - b->type);
416 else
417 return (i);
418 } else
419 return (i);
420}

425}

427int ASN1_STRING_type(const ASN1_STRING *str)
